                            <comment id="17084443" author="becket_qin" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2020 00:11:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to make it clear, the root cause of the OOM in the ticket description was due to #&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-9700&quot; title=&quot;Negative estimatedCompressionRatio leads to misjudgment about if there is no room&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-9700&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-9700&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This ticket added an optimization to release the compression buffer when splitting a large &lt;tt&gt;ProducerBatch&lt;/tt&gt;. Because this is just an optimization, we are not cherry-picking it to earlier release branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
